1 Introduction

Thank you for joining us for this 16S rRNA microbiome data processing tutorial! Before we jump in, letâs start by going over our learning objectives for the technical part of our training.

  • Check the Quality of Your Microbiome Data

  • Develop Amplicon Sequence Variants (ASVs) using Divisive Amplicon Denoising Algorithm (DADA2)

  • Assign taxonomy to the species level

  • Make a phylogenetic tree

  • Collate this data in a phyloseq object for later analysis

This tutorial is designed to introduce you to the nuts and bolts of processing microbiome data. You may find that after you finish this tutorial, you start processing your data through other pipelines like Nephele1, but hopefully some of the concepts we cover today will guide how you approach and review your data.
